Doc: The acceptable tolerance in the delivered quantity of a physical commodity product in terms of a percentage of the agreed delivery quantity.

Source.Contents:
/#
   The acceptable tolerance in the delivered quantity of a physical commodity product in terms of a percentage of the agreed delivery quantity.
 #/
record FpML5.reporting.PercentageTolerance {
  # The maximum percentage amount by which the quantity delivered can exceed the agreed quantity.
  postitive : decimal?

  # The maximum percentage amount by which the quantity delivered can be less than the agreed quantity.
  negative : decimal?

  # Indicates whether the tolerance it at the seller's or buyer's option.
  option : FpML5.reporting.PartyReference?

}

postitive.Doc: The maximum percentage amount by which the quantity delivered can exceed the agreed quantity.
postitive.Name: postitive

negative.Doc: The maximum percentage amount by which the quantity delivered can be less than the agreed quantity.
negative.Name: negative

option.Doc: Indicates whether the tolerance it at the seller's or buyer's option.
option.Name: option
